headline: KEYS Q1 Earnings Call: Revenue Misses, AI and Data Center Demand Drive Outlook
summary: Electronic measurement provider Keysight (NYSE:KEYS) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 7.4% year on year to $1.31 billion. Its non-GAAP EPS of $1.70 per share was 3.3% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
